node.text:

node.text:
The number of hours of proper practice that some researchers believe it takes to become an expert at anything. I'm nowhere near there yet. It takes passion and dedication to achieve success in any given field, and the more you enjoy your work or endeavour, the easier it is to put in the required time.

Thanks for watching!  New videos every week. 

To see what I’m up to during the rest of the week, please follow me on my other online channels;

Website: http://myselfreliance.com/​
Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/c/ShawnJamesMySelfReliance/

node.text: How I built my off grid log cabin. In this video, the first in a series showing the complete build from the first cut to the last addition, I explain what logs I used, how I cut the saddle joints, what chinking recipe worked the best and how I made pine tar.

node.text: Following up on the attempted break-in at the log cabin, I talk about the importance of being prepared for smaller and medium sized emergencies rather than focusing on major events and catastrophes.

node.title: Self Reliance and Prepping for Emergencies at the Log Cabin

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Shawn James on July 02, 2021 tagging @norwoodsawmills. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: One of the few things I took from the old cabin to use at the new homestead was a couple of ash logs for hardwood flooring in the new cabin. This week, I milled the floor boards to give them time to dry before installing them next spring. Click on the link in my bio to watch the full @youtube video.

node.text: I guess it’s time to finish the fence around my vegetable garden and orchard!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Shawn James on June 30, 2021. May be an image of tree and outdoors.

node.text: That’s my sketch book in my hands. A question I get asked daily is, do I work from plans for my buildings? In my latest video on my Shawn James YouTube channel, I show my sketch book for my new cabin.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Shawn James on June 27, 2021 tagging @swiftcanoeandkayak. May be an image of 1 person and nature.

node.text: Cooling off before the monsoons started. After a dry and warm winter and spring, we’re now getting several days of record rainfall. This should help water levels in local waterways.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Shawn James on June 26, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, outdoors and tree.

node.text: I look like I’ve been working in a coal mine. I am almost done building the cabin basement using charred wood so I can move on to cleaner construction methods. On my Shawn James @youtube channel, I have a new video explaining how and why I built a basement in this cabin.
